\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s12\cf0\sl-533\slmult0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb5\rtlch\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs22\lang0\i0\b0\*\cs30\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f0\fs22\lang0\loch\f0\fs22\lang0 The application brought by appellant concerns the question as to whether the transaction is notifiable as being a large merger as defined in section 12 of the Act. If it is found to be a large merger, the Tribunal is required to approve the merger or to pr
ohibit implementation thereof in terms of section 16(1) of the Act. Assuming that the proposed transaction in this case amounts to a large merger and that the Tribunal is required to approve thereof, the question arises as to the powers of the Tribunal in 
circumstances where a party intends to implement a large merger in contravention of the Act, particularly S 13 A thereof.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s12\cf0\sl-528\slmult0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb53\rtlch\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs22\lang0\i0\b0\*\cs30\cf0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f0\fs22\lang0\loch\f0\fs22\lang0 Section 13 A provides: 'The parties to an intermediate or large merger may not implement that merger until it has been approved with or without conditions, by the Competition Commission in terms of section 14(1)(b), the Competition Tribunal in terms of sec
tion 16(2) or the Competition Appeal Court in terms of section 17.'}
